The paper focuses on object recognition using online recognition platforms and investigates their reliability under different conditions. This topic falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.MM) sub-categories. The paper also introduces a framework that utilizes both handcrafted features and deep neural networks, which falls under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of the framework, which involves similarity estimation, falling under information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
